                <note type="abstract">Analyzes the use of the Arabic Energicus modal form in the Arabic translation of the bilingual Arabic-Coptic Ms. Paris, Bibliothèque nationale de France, Copt. 1. Links the use of the Engergicus, which is supposed to be out of use in medieval Arabic, with certain Coptic verb forms as well as with classical Arabic style influenced by the Quran in keeping with the findings of Tamar Zewi regarding Saadiah Gaon's Pentateuch translation (see {https://www.zotero.org/groups/biblia_arabica/items/itemKey/NEPDMG3G}).</note>
